<p>If I need to override a color in a brush, I would set it into App.xaml like this:</p>  <pre><code>   &lt;ResourceDictionary&gt;             &lt;ResourceDictionary.ThemeDictionaries&gt;                 &lt;ResourceDictionary x:Key="Light"&gt;                     &lt;SolidColorBrush x:Key="PivotHeaderForegroundUnselectedBrush" Color="#A7A9AC" /&gt;                     &lt;SolidColorBrush x:Key="PivotHeaderForegroundSelectedBrush" Color="Black" /&gt;                 &lt;/ResourceDictionary&gt;             &lt;/ResourceDictionary.ThemeDictionaries&gt;         &lt;/ResourceDictionary&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The editor underlines <code>&lt;ResourceDictionary&gt;</code> saying: "Each dictionary entry must have an associated key".</p>  <p>How can solve this?</p>